<TITLE> BB puts freeze on Hizbut Tahrir accounts </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 25 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh Bank instructed all banks to freeze accounts of the recently banned Hizb ut-Tahrir for one month. A letter from the central bank to all chief executives of private, government, specialised and foreign banks conveyed this instruction. "If any bank holds accounts of the banned Hizbut Tahrir or anyone related to this organisation then all transactions of these accounts must be frozen for a month," the letter said. The central bank gave the order under the Anti Terrorism Act. Hizbut Tahrir was banned by the Bangladesh government on Oct 22, which said the group was a threat to national safety. Police on Sunday seized office equipment and materials from the Dhaka head quarters and Sylhet office of the Islamic outfit. bd
